body_html:
@AndreaFar I don't think this problem is TensorFlow-specific, because the TensorFlow binaries do not include any HDF5 support. It's possible that one of the libraries TensorFlow depends on is not working. (Perhaps Pands? It seems to have had similar problems in the past....) Therefore it might be possible to fix this by upgrading your other installed packages and/or the copy of HDF5 that seems to be installed in C:\Program Files\HDF5.

If you continue to have problems, please feel free to open another issue with more details about your configuration.

body:
@AndreaFar I don't think this problem is TensorFlow-specific, because the TensorFlow binaries do not include any HDF5 support. It's possible that one of the libraries TensorFlow depends on is not working. (Perhaps Pands? It seems to have had similar [problems in the past](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/3091)....) Therefore it might be possible to fix this by upgrading your other installed packages and/or the copy of HDF5 that seems to be installed in `C:\Program Files\HDF5`.

If you continue to have problems, please feel free to open another issue with more details about your configuration.
